The expungement was part of the reason for my downvote (although not the primary reason). I can feel this potentially becoming a bit of a hobby horse for me - it is ludicrous for the Foundation to expunge critical information like where a skip is located or what it does to a person, because expunged information is irretrievably lost to the Foundation. Redaction is almost always the more correct option, even in the narrow range of cases where hiding information is effective from a technical writing perspective.







